<div id="post-2443" class="post-2443 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-science">
<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/" title="Permalink to Rio+20 stuck on traffic for a year, every&nbsp;day" rel="bookmark">Rio+20 stuck on traffic for a year, every&nbsp;day</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta">
<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/" title="9:28 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">June 24, 2012</span></a> <span class="by-author"><span class="sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="{{site.baseurl}}author/nasonurb/" title="View all posts by brunosan" rel="author">brunosan</a></span> </span> </div> 
<div class="entry-content">
<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 510px"><img src="http://farm5.staticflickr.com/4090/4993990030_b10fd201bb.jpg" alt="rio traffic" width="500" height="375"/><p class="wp-caption-text">Traffic in Rio de Janeiro</p></div>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Rio+20 [<a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/26/rio20-where-the-side-events-are-the-main-event/">my post about the conference</a> here, this is a rant on the traffic] had 45.381 participants from 188 countries, which included 100 heads of state and their staff [<a href="http://blogs.un.org/blog/2012/06/22/rio20-wrap-up-vital-stats/">source</a>]. Now, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rio_de_Janeiro">the city of Rio de Janerio</a> has 6 million people, and 2 million cars, in 5000 km². Furthermore, there seems to be a <a href="http://brazilianbubble.com/opinion-brazils-strained-auto-loan-market">automobile loan bubble</a>, similar to the house loan bubble in the USA, that has been injecting cars into the barely increasing roads of the city. You can already see how logistics in Rio+20 are, at least, very tricky.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"> <a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/#more-2443" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
<div id="geo-post-2443" class="geo geo-post" style="display: none">
<span class="latitude">38.910000</span>
<span class="longitude">-77.018000</span>
</div><div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-rating-enabled sd-like-enabled sd-sharing-enabled"><div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing"><h3 class="sd-title">Share this:</h3><div class="sd-content"><ul><li class="share-twitter"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-twitter sd-button share-icon" href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/?share=twitter" title="Click to share on Twitter" id="sharing-twitter-2443"><span>Twitter</span></a></li><li class="share-facebook"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-facebook sd-button share-icon" href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/?share=facebook" title="Share on Facebook" id="sharing-facebook-2443"><span>Facebook</span></a></li><li class="share-google-plus-1"><div class="googleplus1_button"><g:plusone size="medium" callback="sharing_plusone" href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/"></g:plusone></div></li><li class="share-reddit"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-reddit sd-button share-icon" href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/?share=reddit" title="Click to share on Reddit"><span>Reddit</span></a></li><li class="share-email"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-email sd-button share-icon" href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/?share=email" title="Click to email this to a friend"><span>Email</span></a></li><li class="share-end"></li></ul><div class="sharing-clear"></div></div></div><div class="wpl-likebox sd-block sd-like"><h3 class="sd-title">Like this:</h3><div class="sd-content"><div id="like-2443" class="wpl-button "><a href='{{site.baseurl}}2012/06/24/logistics-and-rio20/?like=1&amp;_wpnonce=bcd53df3d6' title='I like this.' class='like needs-login sd-button' rel='nofollow'><span>Like</span></a></div><div class="wpl-count sd-like-count">Be the first to like this.</div></div></div></div> </div> 
