<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/05/18/scientific-value-%e2%89%a0-perception-of-the-scientific-value/" title="Permalink to Scientific value ≠ Perception of the scientific&nbsp;value" rel="bookmark">Scientific value ≠ Perception of the scientific&nbsp;value</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta">
<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/05/18/scientific-value-%e2%89%a0-perception-of-the-scientific-value/" title="8:34 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">May 18, 2012</span></a> <span class="by-author"><span class="sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="{{site.baseurl}}author/nasonurb/" title="View all posts by brunosan" rel="author">brunosan</a></span> </span> </div> 
<div class="entry-content">
<p>A russian satellite makes a time lapse of the Earth from space. A truly beautiful video.<br/>
<span class='embed-youtube' style='text-align:center; display: block;'><iframe class='youtube-player' type='text/html' width='640' height='390' src='http://www.youtube.com/embed/6twFHqJ03_k?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;fs=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;wmode=transparent' frameborder='0'></iframe></span></p>
<p>This reminds me of a text I read many years ago: Carl Sagan was defending the inclusion of visual cameras in scientific payloads, even when the scientific value would be arguable.</p>
<p> <a href="{{site.baseurl}}2012/05/18/scientific-value-%e2%89%a0-perception-of-the-scientific-value/#more-2393" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
